cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the design of cryptoeconomic systems, which involves aspects of cryptography (cs.CR), game theory (cs.GT), distributed computing (cs.DC), social networks (cs.SI), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The focus on evidence-based decision making suggests a strong emphasis on empirical methods and data analysis, which further supports the relevance of these sub-categories.
